│ But looking at the code, the folding functions seem to only replace/erase the current instruction.                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Unless... in the `replaceValue` function, when it calls `Worklist.pushUsersToWorkList(*NewI)`, it might be adding instructions that are then processed and erased during the same iteration.                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ But that should be handled by the worklist being processed after the main loop.                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ I think I need to make a targeted fix. Let me check if there's a specific issue with how the pass handles reduction intrinsics with constant arguments.                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Upon closer inspection, I recall that in LLVM, reduction intrinsics with constant arguments should be constant-folded by the constant folder, not by VectorCombine.                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ So VectorCombine should not be trying to process them.                                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The fix is to add a check in the reduction folding functions to return early if the operand is a constant.                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Let me modify `foldShuffleFromReductions` to add this check.                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ sed -i '3045i\  // If the operand is a constant, let constant folding handle it.\n  if (isa<Constant>(I.getOperand(0)))\n    return false;' ./llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                            │
